reviews.review: I'm baffled by the bad reviews... I thought this was the best of the trilogy. My only issue is it felt a bit rushed.. ideally if we could delete the last Jedi from existence and just have this one split over 2 movies would have been perfect.
It's what I wanted to see. I've loved it.
It felt rushed, the story was not getting me and they made characters feel to strong
Disgrace to the first 6 films and the name Star Wars.

Tal vez muchos me tilden de loco, pero como fiel fan de ésta saga iniciada hace más de 42 años, me atrevo a decir que ésta película es un digno cierre no solo para la trilogía, sino para toda la saga Skywalker. De principio a fin me tuvo al filo de butaca, me hizo sonreír y llorar, provocó en mí un cúmulo de emociones y sentimientos inexplicable. Es maravillosa.

The cringe in this one was over the top. It had some cool moments but most of it was random. And there was a pattern: someone dies, somebody kisses someone for no reason, then another death, then another kiss. They really tried to please the fans with some references to the original movies. However, half the time I was wondering if I am watching Star Wars or a random Disney movie.

Against all odds, JJ absolutely nailed this movie! I was mesmerised back in 77 as a 5 year old kid during episode 4 and again tonight watching episode 9, I was totally captivated, ending the Skywalker saga on a massive high.
How our Princess was handled was absolutely perfect, the movie looked incredible, the cast were all amazing and John Williams score, as always, was consistently awesome. I left the theatre this evening with a tear in my eye and a huge grin on my face.
My 13 year old daughter scored the film 10/10, my 18 year old son 8.5/10, my wife 9/10 and for me it was a perfect 5 star experience. I'm going back to see it again tomorrow, to once again take in that stunningly beautiful final Star Wars shot, in all it's emotional glory.
Star Wars has been a massive part of my life and tonight the saga ended with me feeling full of wonder, awe and absolute total satisfaction; thanks JJ.
Once again the majority of movie critics have demonstrated their irrelevance!
spent most of the time thinking how to express "?????" irl
This is a whole lot of movie. But I don't think I could have asked for more. And ultimately, it honoured the spirit and message of the original – Believe in yourself!
This was offensive, not a single interesting character arc, if at all. More plot holes than every movie I've seen, and a disgusting kiss near the end. This is a disgrace.
